timing_enable_...ew_derate_mode(25.10)  timing_enable_...ew_derate_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_vtskew_derate_mode

Syntax
       timing_enable_vtskew_derate_mode

       {true | false}

       Default : false

       Enables voltage threshold (VT) skew analysis.

       When  set  to  true,  the software analyzes the effects of VT skew in a
       multi-VT environment.

       Due to variations in the manufacturing process, the  voltage  threshold
       (Vth)  of a given Vth class (e.g., SVT, LVT, ULVT) can show some varia-
       tions that might result in cells of that class operating either  faster
       or  slower  than the nominal value.  The Tempus Vth skew analysis auto-
       mates the process of selecting which Vth permutations need to  be  run,
       which  ensures  a  robust  analysis  and  optimizes the software to run
       faster and efficiently.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

